{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bec2a439-5f5c-4ade-ba74-def8598437ac","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — reruns tests automatically when you save a file.\n- **`dotnet watch run`** — for apps, applies changes without restarting.\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` execute once and exit; they don't monitor for file changes. The `watch` command is what provides the hot reload behavior.\n\nFor your test project, try:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e7eccd60-57fd-4a80-9851-d41d07bb2f5f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET hot reload - specifically whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` to benefit from hot reload. Let me look at the project files to understand the context better.","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"9839:250B0D:29B0F6:3683E4:69FFE24D"},"id":"b5ec223b-0d60-413c-85d4-ddd2870379a2","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:41:38.149Z","parentId":"0a1d7180-526d-49e3-bcd8-9aedd08a7b4a"}
